Class RandomizedQueue<Item>

  • java.lang.Object
    • bilal.onlinecourses.algorithmpt1.prog.assignment2.RandomizedQueue<Item>
  • Type Parameters:
    Item - the generic type of an item in this bag
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Item>

    public class RandomizedQueue<Item>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Item>
    Created by Bilal on 2/18/2016. The RandomizedQueue class is a randomized queue similar to a stack or queue except that the item removed is chosen uniformly at random from items in the data structure It supports enqueue, dequeue and sample operations and iterating through the items in random order.

    This implementation uses a resizing array, which double the underlying array when it is full and halves the underlying array when it is one-quarter full. The enqueue, size, sample, and is-empty operations all take constant time in the worst case while dequeue operation most cM steps in the worst case, for some constant c.

    Author:
    Bilal Abdullah
